Definition.WordDefinition:
Li \Li\ (l[=e]), n. 1. A Chinese measure of distance, being a little more than one third of a mile. [1913 Webster]
2. A Chinese copper coin; a cash. See {Cash}. [1913 Webster]

Definition.WordDefinition: Puntello \Pun*tel"lo\, n.; pl. {-li}. [It., dim. of punto point.] (Sculpture) One of the points sometimes drilled as guides for cutting away superfluous stone. [Webster 1913 Suppl.]
